  • Super Bright & Glare-free LED Light : Lepotec LED cabinet lights, this panel light contains 54 hidden lamp beads (up to 350 lumens), which are invisible and will not blind your eyes. The natural and soft light provides perfect illumination for your safety and convenience at home.
  • Infrared Sensor Smart Home Night Light : The 54 LED light has 3 modes: Motion Sensor Mode (G mode), Always-On Mode (On mode), and Off Mode. Under G mode, the light can detect the motion of a human in the dark and will be auto-on within 16 feet, auto-off after 20 seconds of no motion detected. Under ON mode, it works as a normal LED light.
  • Easy to Install and Recharge : The Built-in magnet on the back of the light allows it to absorb on any iron surface. Or stick it on any non-iron surface with the included 3M Adhesive Magnetic strip. without any tools, screws or nuts are required. When you need to charge or change place, you can take it off easily for any dark dark closet, cupboard or pantry.
  • Rechargable & Large Battery Capacity : The built-in 2500 mAh high-capacity rechargeable battery can last for up to 6 hours under ON Mode and last up to 2-4 weeks under G mode after fully charged. It can be easily charged via the USB cable in the laptop or power bank.
  • Wide Application:The multifunctional light makes it the best night lights and flashlight for your bedroom,bathroom,dining room ,laundry room,lazy Susan,closet, cabinet, corridor, workshop, basement, garage, stairwell,garage entrances pantry,kitchen in the dark.

Product description

LEPOTEC--Make Your Life Convenient & Bright

LEPOTEC LED under cabinet light contains 54 energy-saving and motion sensing ,Built in Magnet Adsorption Aluminum LED Panel Super Bright, Ultra Thin, Glare-Free LEDs to illuminate dark areas, ideal for the bedroom, wardrobe, closet, cabinet, workshop, kitchen cupboards, bookcase, shed, garage, hallway, kitchen, sink, stairway, laundry, drawers etc.

Motion Sensor:In bright light environment(daytime),the inductor will not be triggered and the light will be off

LEPOTEC wireless motion sensor led light can be used in anywhere


USB Rechargeable

Built-in 2500mAh high-capacity rechargeable battery,easily charged via the USB cable(incluede),the cabinet lights can last for about 6 hours after fully charged.


Wireless Motion Sensor

With a built-in thermosensitive infrared sensor and a light sensor function module, the lamp can be turned on automatically when a moving person is detected and turned off 20s after the person moves out of the induction zone.


3 Modes Adjustable LED Closet Lights

Motion Sensing/Instant On/Instant Off,can be used ans normal night Light or motion sensor light.


LED strip

Built-in light guide plate, uniform and soft light, no glare and flicker, Body sensing range 3-5M (10 feet) / 120 SMD LED Lamp beads are used for the sake of energy-saving operation and longer service life.


Magnetic absorption

Built-in magnet, you can directly make the cabinet light absorb on all iron artcle surface;Or you can use the included double-sided 3M tape and iron sheet to stick on any non-iron article surface,When need charge or change place you can take it off anytime.


Wide Applications

These multi-functional under cabinet lights are ideal for the bedrom,baby room,closet,cabinet,corridor,workshop,basement,garage,stairwell,oil depots,door,garage entrances and other places.


Specification

  • Material: Aviation aluminum + ABS panel
  • Body color: matte silver Light color: cool white light
  • LEDs: SMD2835
  • LED Lumen: 350lm
  • Detecting Angle: 120 degree
  • Detecting Distance : up to 3-5m (about 10ft)
  • LED Life Time : more than 60000h
  • Battery: 2500mAh lithium battery


How to used ON/OFF/AUTO Mode for this Motion Sensor Light?

> Mode 1 (Always On): Turn the toggle switch to the "ON" position > Mode 2 ( Motion Sensor): Turn the toggle switch to the "G" position In this mode, the LED is off after 20 seconds. > Mode 3 (OFF): Turn the toggle switch to the "OFF" position


What You Get

LEPOTEC Under Cabinet Light /3M Adhesive Magnetic Strip/USB Cable/User Manual

The motion detection feature receives mixed feedback - while some love it for navigating dark kitchens, others report it stops working after a few days. The turn-on time is also mixed, with some units shutting off after 30 seconds.

    • JP
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Unbelievable Performance
      Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
      Color: Silver-RGBSize: 10'' 45RGB(2 Pack)
      ---FINAL UPDATE March 2025: The battery finally died March 1st after roughly 20 months on a single charge in a refrigerator for the entire time. The light turned on with motion roughly 2,000 times and had a total "on" time of roughly 19.5 hours (see how I... See more
      ---FINAL UPDATE March 2025:

      The battery finally died March 1st after roughly 20 months on a single charge in a refrigerator for the entire time. The light turned on with motion roughly 2,000 times and had a total "on" time of roughly 19.5 hours (see how I got those numbers in the update from Nov 2024). The light was noticeably dimmer around mid January and it took on a yellowish color in mid February (instead of the "cool" white I had it set to).

      If you are using these lights for the motion setting, you have absolutely nothing to worry about with regards to how long they will last. However, if you have them set to be on all the time then they will probably only last about a day if you are lucky. Personally, I think that's the wrong way to use these lights though. There are better options for always-on lights. These are definitely meant for shorter periods of activity, either set with motion detection or perhaps using the colors to add atmosphere or mood to a situation.

      As I said in my earlier reviews, I have no complaints whatsoever and quite literally couldn't be happier with my purchase. If you need motion activated lights, 100% get these.

      ---UPDATE Nov 2024:

      It's been about a year since my original review (see below) and about 16 months since I bought these lights. The motion activated light in my mini fridge is still on the original charge from 16 months ago. Estimating the light turning on 3 or 4 times per day or roughly 100 times a month, that's roughly 1,600 times the light has come on, without fail, on a single charge.

      To be fair, the light only stays on for about 30 seconds after it stops detecting motion so estimating 35 seconds of "on" time each time the fridge was opened (a few seconds to grab something then the 30 seconds after no motion detected) only puts it at about 15.5 hours of "on" time. However, that is extremely impressive to me considering it hasn't been charged in 16 months and is stored in a cold environment which typically hurts battery life. Still no issues with the adhesive plates for the magnets either.

      I very rarely bother to review anything but it felt necessary for this product. I was impressed a year ago when I first reviewed it but now I'm blown away. There is no possible way for me to be happier with this product. I'm very curious to see how long this one battery charge lasts and will update again when it finally dies.

      ---Original Review from Nov 2023:

      I bought these lights because a cheap mini fridge I bought didn't have a light inside. I mounted one of the lights to the ceiling of the fridge, close to the door, set to come on with motion. Because of the ledge at the top of the fridge's door, simply opening the door triggers the motion detector and the light comes on providing the perfect amount of light for my little 2.6 cu ft refrigerator. I used the included adhesive metal plates to attach the light since it has built in magnets.

      I fully charged the light before installing and 4 months later I have not had to recharge the light yet. I open the fridge on average 3 or 4 times every single day and have done that for 4 months. That's at least 400 times that the light has come on and all on a single charge. On top of that, it's inside of a roughly 42F fridge and batteries don't really perform as well when cold but it's still going strong anyway. The adhesive has been strong and problem free as well, even with the cold environment and taking the full weight of the light since it's mounted on the ceiling.

      Even if it dies tomorrow and needs a recharge, I have zero complaints about battery life. The option of choosing any color you want is nice too, however I just use mine on a "cool" white setting. These lights have far exceeded my expectations and are well worth the money in my opinion. I'm currently only using one of the two lights that came in the pack but if I found a use for more of these I would buy these again without hesitation.

      I love these; they have been in constant use for two years.
